	<body>
		<div class="outer">
			<h1>Gliders in Life-Like Cellular Automata</h1>

			<div class="inner">
				<p>This is an online database of gliders
				(moving patterns that remain bounded in size)
				in two dimensional cellular automaton rules such as
				<a href="rules/b3s23/">Conway's life.</a></p>

				<p>The following access methods are available:</p>

				<ul>
					<li><a href="/ca/rules/">Form-based interface to select rules</a></li>
					<li><a href="/ca/rules/list.html">List of interesting evolution rules</a></li>
					<li>Lists of interesting gliders:
					<ul>
						<li><a href="/ca/gliders/smallest.html">Smallest known gliders</a></li>
						<li><a href="/ca/gliders/biggest.html">Biggest known gliders</a></li>
						<li><a href="/ca/gliders/slowest.html">Slowest known gliders</a></li>
						<li><a href="/ca/gliders/jumpiest.html">Gliders that move the farthest each period</a></li>
						<li><a href="/ca/gliders/highper.html">Gliders with the highest known periods</a></li>
						<li><a href="/ca/gliders/versatile.html">Gliders that work in the most rules</a></li>
						<li><a href="/ca/gliders/knightships.html">Gliders with unusual slopes</a></li>
					</ul></li>
				</ul>

				<p>For more information, a standalone C version of the database,
				and pointers to search software for finding these patterns, see
				<a href="http://www.ics.uci.edu/~eppstein/ca/">my main cellular automaton page</a>.</p>
			</div>

			<div class="credit">
